FBIS4-52204 "dreas089_c_94025" FBIS-EAS-94-089 Daily Report 6 May 1994 North Korea Reminiscences of Kim Il-song Published in China Reminiscences of Kim Il-song Published in China SK0605051094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0435 GMT 6 May 94 SK0605051094 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 6 (KCNA) -- Vols. 1 and 2 of Part 1 "The Anti-Japanese Revolution" of the great leader President Kim Il-song's reminiscences "With the Century" were published in one book by the social science publishing house of China in April. A picture of President Kim Il-song standing on a lakeside is printed on the front cover of the book. Carried on the front and back covers of the book are the propositions of President Kim Il-song "Revolutionaries, believe in the people and rely on them at all times and you shall always emerge victorious; if you are forsaken by them, you will always fail. Let this be your maxim in your life and struggle" and "The destiny of a nation can be saved only through the unity and struggle of all the forces that love their country and treasure their nation."
